# .env.local — Environment Variables
#
# ⚠️ TRAINING PURPOSES ONLY — these are not real API keys.
# This file is here to show you what a .env.local file looks like.
#
# ---
#
# HOW TO USE THIS FILE:
# 1. Copy this file and rename it to .env.local in the root of your project
# 2. Replace the example values below with your real API keys
# 3. Never commit .env.local to GitHub — it should already be in your .gitignore
# 4. Add these same variables in Vercel: Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#
# ---

# Gemini API (Google AI)
# Get your key at: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=AIzaSyExampleKeyNotReal1234567890abcdef

# Weather API (OpenWeatherMap)
# Get your key at: https://openweathermap.org/api
WEATHER_API_KEY=abc123exampleweatherkeynotreal456789

# Your app's public URL (no trailing slash)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://helloworld.com
